22
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:50,360
- Why? 
- Because Antonis is waiting. You know what 
he told me on the phone?

23
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:53,380
"You laid three families on me and you are enjoying your freedom in Thessaloniki."

24
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:54,340
- Why didn't you tell him...

25
00:02:54,340 --> 00:02:58,440
..."you hillbilly. You Peloponessian dirtbag.
Each time you are seperate with Eleni"...

26
00:02:58,460 --> 00:03:02,580
..."don't we have to put up with her along with your kids and your mother?" 
- I didn't tell him Panos because he is right.

27
00:03:02,620 --> 00:03:04,960
You know how hard it is to take 
nine kids to the beach each day...

28
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:08,300
...to shop for sixteen people, 
to take the seniors to the swings?

29
00:03:08,300 --> 00:03:11,020
- He takes the seniors to the swings?! 
- Along with the kids.

30
00:03:11,020 --> 00:03:15,780
Of course, the seniors don't swing but they enjoy watching 
and during the evening they want to have hamburgers at the square.

31
00:03:15,780 --> 00:03:18,380
If it was me, I would have killed someone. 
- Let him kill his mother!

32
00:03:18,380 --> 00:03:21,000
You know what she told me on Easter when I cut some kokoretsi for her?

33
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:23,920
"Come to Padaditsa and see 
how real kokoretsi tastes like."

34
00:03:23,920 --> 00:03:26,880
- Indeed, in Papaditsa the kokoretsi is out of this world.

35
00:03:26,900 --> 00:03:27,600
- Out of this world?

36
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:30,220
You know what a professional from Kalamata told me?

37
00:03:30,220 --> 00:03:31,260
I ask him...

38
00:03:31,260 --> 00:03:34,400
..."How come Mr. Marmatzeas is the kokoretsi in Padaditsa so delicious?"...

39
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:36,000
...And he replies tete a tete...

40
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:38,240
..."Because in Papaditsa they don't wash the entrails".

41
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:39,320
- That means we are eating...

42
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:41,060
- Grilled shit with mustard and pepper...

43
00:03:41,060 --> 00:03:42,320
...that's what we are eating!

44
00:03:46,420 --> 00:03:47,400
Because...

45
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:49,200
...look at what God did.

46
00:03:49,200 --> 00:03:50,380
He creates three sisters.

47
00:03:50,380 --> 00:03:52,020
I take the first, all right.

48
00:03:52,020 --> 00:03:54,160
You take the next. All right.

49
00:03:54,160 --> 00:03:55,920
And then comes he during the PASOK pre-congress...

50
00:03:55,920 --> 00:03:58,080
...And marries the youngest. 
- That's how we became brothers-in-law.

51
00:03:58,080 --> 00:03:59,960
- Yes! But, what have I ever done...

52
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:03,680
...to become family with an alderman 
from Papaditsa, Lakonia?

53
00:04:05,900 --> 00:04:08,400
Don't stop...

54
00:04:11,220 --> 00:04:13,840
Stop. Stop!

55
00:04:28,840 --> 00:04:30,640
Sir, I'm afraid we made a mistake.

56
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:34,680
How may I help you?

57
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:36,460
Sir, I'm afraid we made a mistake.

58
00:04:36,460 --> 00:04:38,560
It is human to err.

59
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:40,540
I was told that, in order to reach Kavala...

60
00:04:40,540 --> 00:04:42,460
...the sea must be on my right.

61
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:44,240
And where is the sea?

62
00:04:44,840 --> 00:04:46,520
On my left.

63
00:04:47,180 --> 00:04:48,520
Is that your dad?

64
00:04:49,980 --> 00:04:51,160
Your heading is correct...

65
00:04:51,160 --> 00:04:53,760
...when you reach Asprovalta, the sea will be on your right...

66
00:04:53,780 --> 00:04:55,620
...this is lake Volvi.

67
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:58,020
Have you ever bathed in the Lake?

68
00:04:58,020 --> 00:04:58,960
- No.

69
00:04:58,960 --> 00:05:00,960
Under the moonlight, the nymphs emerge.

70
00:05:00,960 --> 00:05:02,960
- It must be magical.

71
00:05:02,960 --> 00:05:04,960
- Magic...

72
00:05:04,960 --> 00:05:08,140
- This must certainly be the place where the historical Volvi Congress took place...

73
00:05:08,140 --> 00:05:09,520
- I'm not sure.

74
00:05:09,520 --> 00:05:13,600
- They say that, this congress was a watershed...

75
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:15,880
...and influenced the political scene.

76
00:05:15,880 --> 00:05:19,560
- Maybe. 
- I thank you nevertheless.

77
00:05:35,080 --> 00:05:36,700
We should come one evening...

78
00:05:36,700 --> 00:05:37,580
...Mister?

79
00:05:37,580 --> 00:05:40,580
Panagiotis. My friends call me "Panos".

80
00:05:40,580 --> 00:05:42,220
...Mr. Panos told me

81
00:05:42,240 --> 00:05:44,080
...that, under the full moon the nymphs emerge...

82
00:05:44,100 --> 00:05:45,780
...and bathe in the water.

83
00:05:45,780 --> 00:05:48,220
Again, I thank you.

84
00:06:12,700 --> 00:06:14,600
You see what God does?

85
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:17,420
Creating creatures like that 
and then unleashing them upon the world.

86
00:06:17,420 --> 00:06:19,760
And He does not care if He takes my breath away.

87
00:06:21,760 --> 00:06:23,500
So, what do I do now?

88
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:25,360
It came as a bit of a suprise, Panos...

89
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:27,880
...But until we reach the ferry, 
we'll have forgotten all about her.

90
00:06:27,880 --> 00:06:29,640
Well, I'm not forgetting her!

91
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:32,660
Time is a doctor, Panos. He passes and he obscures everything.

92
00:06:32,660 --> 00:06:36,660
Now you must preoccupy yourself with other things
and remove her from your thoughts.

93
00:06:42,320 --> 00:06:44,360
<i>Get out of my thought...</i>

94
00:06:44,360 --> 00:06:46,680
<i>...everything that is you hurts...</i>

95
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:51,960
<i>...since you are living with someone else.</i>

96
00:06:51,960 --> 00:06:53,960
<i>I don't need anything...</i>

97
00:06:53,960 --> 00:06:56,700
<i>...what are you looking for anymore...</i>

98
00:06:56,740 --> 00:07:00,740
<i>...and are still torturing me?</i>

99
00:07:03,920 --> 00:07:06,800
<i>Get out of my head...</i>

100
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:08,800
<i>...the wounds are not enough for you...</i>

101
00:07:08,840 --> 00:07:11,400
<i>...that I touch and it hurts...</i>

102
00:07:11,420 --> 00:07:14,820
<i>...Get out of my head.</i>

103
00:07:14,840 --> 00:07:17,000
<i>Get out! Get out! Get out!</i>

104
00:07:17,580 --> 00:07:19,860
<i>Get out of my head...</i>

105
00:07:19,860 --> 00:07:22,220
<i>...the wounds are not enough for you...</i>

106
00:07:22,220 --> 00:07:24,780
<i>...that because of you I count...</i>

107
00:07:24,780 --> 00:07:29,380
<i>Get out of my head...</i>

108
00:07:29,400 --> 00:07:31,600
<i>Get out! Get out! Get out!</i>

109
00:08:34,700 --> 00:08:38,800
- Panos, I think it would be better if we drank our coffee in Kavala. 
- I'll drink it wherever I want to drink it!

110
00:08:38,800 --> 00:08:43,160
And if someone calls saying we are late
I will also have something to say about his momma.

111
00:08:43,180 --> 00:08:44,740
Good day.

112
00:09:14,800 --> 00:09:17,720
 Something's on your mind.

113
00:09:17,720 --> 00:09:19,560
Didn't you get what happened?

114
00:09:19,560 --> 00:09:22,320
The girl tells him "let's come 
during a full moon night"...

115
00:09:22,320 --> 00:09:24,160
..."the Sir told me", while pointing at me...

116
00:09:24,160 --> 00:09:25,640
...and I say "Panagiotis"...

117
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:27,800
..."My friends call me Panos"...

118
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:29,280
...and the girl says...

119
00:09:29,280 --> 00:09:31,620
..."Mr. <i>Panos</i> told me..."...

120
00:09:31,620 --> 00:09:32,780
You got it?

121
00:09:32,780 --> 00:09:35,120
- Get what?
-Get what?! She didn't say "Mr. Panagiotis"...

122
00:09:35,180 --> 00:09:36,820
...she said "Mr. <i>Panos</i>".

123
00:09:36,820 --> 00:09:38,820
- Are you getting it now?
-No.

124
00:09:38,820 --> 00:09:40,900
Doesn't matter. Because <i>he</i> got it.

125
00:09:40,900 --> 00:09:43,280
...and when he hears "Mr. <i>Panos</i> told me"...

126
00:09:43,280 --> 00:09:46,600
...he thinks to himself "this is getting serious"
and he steps on the gas pedal and zooms away.

127
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:47,680
Indeed, he left in a hurry.

128
00:09:47,680 --> 00:09:52,540
So, think first, understand, and then say 
"I don't understand"!

129
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:57,780
Frappé, ice cold, two spoons of sugar.

130
00:09:57,780 --> 00:09:59,240
The same, no sugar.

131
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:01,240
Panos, Frappé with no sugar is poison.

132
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:02,780
I'll do whatever I want!

133
00:10:13,020 --> 00:10:17,800
<i>Don't say a word...</i>

134
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:20,700
<i>...just let me go...</i>

135
00:10:20,700 --> 00:10:22,900
- We are listening to the same song. 
- Of course.

136
00:10:22,900 --> 00:10:25,400
And <i>he</i> knows we are listening to the same song.

137
00:10:25,400 --> 00:10:27,400
Who Panos?

138
00:10:27,420 --> 00:10:32,280
<i>...empty words that you are used to saying.</i>

139
00:10:33,640 --> 00:10:35,000
<i>...and don't speak...</i>

140
00:10:35,060 --> 00:10:37,440
- Excuse me.
- Good day.
- Good day...

141
00:10:37,440 --> 00:10:38,760
...is this a radio?

142
00:10:38,760 --> 00:10:40,240
CD.

143
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:42,680
<i>...don't tell me, don't tell me...</i>

144
00:10:42,860 --> 00:10:46,640
<i>...that you'll rebuild what you destroyed...</i>

145
00:10:46,640 --> 00:10:49,220
<i>Don't speak, don't speak...</i>

146
00:10:49,220 --> 00:10:49,980
<i>...only with words...</i>

147
00:10:49,980 --> 00:10:51,980
Panos?

148
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:54,920
Panos?

149
00:10:56,320 --> 00:10:58,440
She shows herself, right?

150
00:10:58,440 --> 00:10:59,840
And she tells me, let's go...

151
00:10:59,840 --> 00:11:01,840
...and it's like my life restarts.

152
00:11:02,980 --> 00:11:04,480
Panos...

153
00:11:04,480 --> 00:11:07,440
...I'm picturing the girl coming 
and telling you "let's go"...

154
00:11:07,440 --> 00:11:09,300
...do you put her in the truck 
and you go?

155
00:11:09,300 --> 00:11:12,200
And she gets black from the filth 
from head to toe?

156
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:13,860
Why aren't you answering?

157
00:11:13,860 --> 00:11:17,800
- Because, I'm waiting to see 
where you are getting with this. 
- I'm not trying to get anywhere...

158
00:11:17,800 --> 00:11:19,320
...I'm just making logical assumptions.

159
00:11:19,320 --> 00:11:21,660
You are going to have to buy a new car. 
Not a Mercedes...

160
00:11:21,660 --> 00:11:24,320
...but certainly a convertible. 
Ten million.

161
00:11:24,320 --> 00:11:27,300
Where are you going to take her? 
Are you going to rent a tiny room in Thasos?

162
00:11:27,300 --> 00:11:28,100
Of course not.

163
00:11:28,100 --> 00:11:29,500
A suite in Porto Carras.

164
00:11:29,500 --> 00:11:31,640
In the evening she will want to go to the casino.

165
00:11:31,640 --> 00:11:32,840
...and if she is on a streak, OK.

166
00:11:32,840 --> 00:11:33,760
But if not?

167
00:11:33,760 --> 00:11:38,140
Are you the one to tell her "play prudently" or will you tell her "go on, I got you"?

168
00:11:38,140 --> 00:11:40,420
I'll tell her "go on, I got you".

169
00:11:40,420 --> 00:11:42,420
And then summer is over...

170
00:11:42,420 --> 00:11:44,520
...and for the winter you go to Thessaloniki...

171
00:11:44,520 --> 00:11:46,600
...you will rent a penthouse in Panorama for her...

172
00:11:46,600 --> 00:11:48,600
...and you will eat in the fine restaurants.

173
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:52,640
You have left a wife and three kids a sick sister and an old father behind you.

174
00:11:52,640 --> 00:11:54,080
They are hungry...

175
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:55,660
...and you are eating in Pringkiponisos...

176
00:11:55,660 --> 00:11:57,820
...and suddenly you see Fotoula and Dionisakis...

177
00:11:57,820 --> 00:11:59,360
...and they are begging at the tables...

178
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:02,540
...What do you do at that moment? 
- I throw a rope and hang myself!

179
00:12:02,540 --> 00:12:07,380
This girl must come from around Phaliro or Glyfada
and you take her with on Sunday 
on a match against Olympiacos...

180
00:12:07,380 --> 00:12:11,240
...and Ivić dives in the penalty area, 
and the Anchovies shout for a penalty shot...

181
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:13,060
...and she is shouting for a penalty too.

182
00:12:13,060 --> 00:12:16,240
What will you do in front of the PAOK fans, lifelong fan? 
- I kill her!

183
00:12:16,240 --> 00:12:18,080
I know you, that is why I theorize.

184
00:12:18,080 --> 00:12:20,080
And, to come back to economical matters...

185
00:12:20,080 --> 00:12:22,300
...what will you do when the car payments are due...

186
00:12:22,300 --> 00:12:27,840
...the bouncing checks from the boutiques, the jewelry stores, 
the night clubs, the florists, the restaurants?

187
00:12:32,900 --> 00:12:36,840
The girl herself, to save you will say 
"Panos, that's it for us".

188
00:12:36,880 --> 00:12:41,380
And you, hurt, alone, one morning you will 
present yourself to the prosecutor.

189
00:12:41,380 --> 00:12:45,060
The sentence will be fifteen years, 
this being your first offense.

190
00:12:45,060 --> 00:12:48,120
One morning the gate will open and you will exit the prison.

191
00:12:48,120 --> 00:12:50,260
You will look down towards Thessaloniki.

192
00:12:50,260 --> 00:12:53,940
Your children will be rehabilitated. 
Marika will be living with someone else.

193
00:12:53,940 --> 00:12:58,180
Your father is dead and your sister is 
incarcerated in some asylum.

194
00:12:58,180 --> 00:13:01,060
And you will walk down to the White Tower...

195
00:13:01,060 --> 00:13:07,140
...you will take a stroll but no one 
will welcome you or greet you.

196
00:13:07,140 --> 00:13:12,040
Because, people do not forgive those who 
due to love have fallen!

197
00:13:17,160 --> 00:13:19,560
- Oh, my God!
- Panos! Panos!

198
00:13:30,840 --> 00:13:32,560
Panos, what in God's name did you do?!

199
00:14:10,660 --> 00:14:13,440
Miss, your name?

200
00:14:13,440 --> 00:14:15,860
- Clytemnestra.
- Ms. Clytemnestra, this same thing...

201
00:14:15,860 --> 00:14:19,340
...has happened to him two more times in the past.
- He trows himself in the lake?

202
00:14:19,340 --> 00:14:22,590
No, in the sea. Once in the Messiniakos and 
once in the Pagasitikos bays.

203
00:14:22,590 --> 00:14:25,540
- For the same reason?
- For... a similar reason.

204
00:14:25,540 --> 00:14:29,690
Let him drink a bitter coffee and take a warm shower and 
then I'll take his blood-pressure, OK?

205
00:14:29,690 --> 00:14:30,860
Thank you a lot.

206
00:14:49,840 --> 00:14:54,620
Panos, sometimes we wonder
"for which of our sins did God create women?"

207
00:14:54,620 --> 00:14:57,640
But, I'm thinking now, 
a woman destroyed you...

208
00:14:57,640 --> 00:15:00,060
...but it is also women who saved you.

209
00:15:10,580 --> 00:15:13,180
We wish for you always to be well.

210
00:15:13,180 --> 00:15:15,460
- Always in good health!
- Amen! 
- Thank you.

211
00:15:15,460 --> 00:15:17,500
- Farewell.
- Thank you very much.

212
00:15:24,780 --> 00:15:26,820
- Get well soon.
- Thank you.

213
00:15:29,980 --> 00:15:31,120
- Hello.
- Hello.

214
00:15:33,320 --> 00:15:35,600
How are you feeling?

215
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:37,600
Getting better...

216
00:15:50,240 --> 00:15:51,640
No!

217
00:16:06,700 --> 00:16:09,920
But, the doctoresses told me to drink bitter coffee.

218
00:16:09,920 --> 00:16:12,200
Yeah, that's what they said Panos.

219
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:17,160
But, when I explained your situation a bit better they said 
"better add four spoons of sugar".

220
00:16:17,160 --> 00:16:19,920
- What situation are you talking about exactly?
- Your situation, Panos.

221
00:16:19,920 --> 00:16:23,440
But, instead of telling them about love et cetera, 
I told them that sometimes...

222
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:26,100
...you develop a kind of obstruction in your heart.
- And what did they say?

223
00:16:26,100 --> 00:16:26,880
They were touched.

224
00:16:26,900 --> 00:16:30,640
Of course, they are doctoresses
and they understood about what kind of obstruction I was talking about.

225
00:16:30,640 --> 00:16:34,020
Because one of them said "God, why can't things like that happen to me as well".

226
00:16:34,020 --> 00:16:36,580
- Things like what?
- How should I know? Things...

227
00:16:38,440 --> 00:16:42,100
Drink so your blood sugar goes up a bit, get some strength into you.

228
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:50,900
- I feel regret.
- No Panos, it's not your fault.

229
00:16:50,900 --> 00:16:52,900
I am paying for my mistakes.

230
00:16:52,900 --> 00:16:56,000
-...Life is at fault for laying out traps for us.
- Because, when he says...

231
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:58,880
..."I was told, to get to Kavala 
the sea must be on my right"...

232
00:16:58,880 --> 00:17:02,420
...I should have told him "that's true, turn back and it will be on your right"...

233
00:17:02,420 --> 00:17:04,960
- Would you direct him the wrong way Panagiotis?
- Of course I would.

234
00:17:04,960 --> 00:17:07,520
He would have reached Platamonas and the girl would have told him...

235
00:17:07,520 --> 00:17:09,380
..."Lakis, the sea is on the left again."

236
00:17:09,380 --> 00:17:10,740
Let's assume his name is Lakis.

237
00:17:10,740 --> 00:17:14,960
He would have gotten out the car, would have asked again and would have been told "turn back my good man"...

238
00:17:14,960 --> 00:17:16,680
..."to go to Kavala the sea must be on your right."

239
00:17:16,680 --> 00:17:19,180
The imbecile would have turned 
again and past Thessaloniki...

240
00:17:19,220 --> 00:17:21,520
...at the Volvi lake, the sea would be on his left yet again.

241
00:17:21,520 --> 00:17:24,620
- We should have fooled him like that Panagiotis.
- Yeah, but then you jump in and say...

242
00:17:24,620 --> 00:17:27,720
..."in Asprovalta the sea will be on your right". 
Why would you do such a thing?!

243
00:17:27,720 --> 00:17:31,580
- Because, people like us Panagiotis do not 
wish evil even to their enemies. 
- Well, I do!

244
00:17:31,600 --> 00:17:36,140
Make him travel back and forth from Platamonas to Volvi 
half a dozen times until he gets crazy, the fool!

245
00:17:36,140 --> 00:17:39,560
We are nice people. We don't wish evil to anyone 
and everyone steps on our throat.

246
00:17:39,560 --> 00:17:42,020
Regret. I feel regret!

247
00:17:42,020 --> 00:17:45,860
<i>I regret it all. I regret it all.</i>

248
00:17:45,860 --> 00:17:49,900
<i>And it's all because of my egoism.</i>

249
00:17:49,900 --> 00:17:53,780
<i>I regret it all. I regret it all.</i>

250
00:17:53,780 --> 00:17:57,660
<i>Now, I pay for my mistakes.</i>

251
00:17:57,660 --> 00:18:00,300
<i>I regret it all. I regret it all.</i> 
Don't pick up!

252
00:18:04,420 --> 00:18:11,180
Antonis? Panos had a sudden malaise. He was feeling down and 
his blood sugar got low. We will be in Kavala...

253
00:18:11,200 --> 00:18:14,820
...in an hour, with the ferry we will be on Thasos at around three or four.

254
00:18:14,820 --> 00:18:18,680
What the hell are you telling him? I could be sitting here with a blood-pressure in the low twenties.

255
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:23,880
- I'm not going anywhere without a doctor taking a look at me first.
 - We can't leave. Yes, there are two doctoresses here.

256
00:18:23,880 --> 00:18:27,880
- What you are saying Antonis? How can you even think of such a thing?!
- What this Arcadian shepherd...

257
00:18:27,880 --> 00:18:30,640
...the Peloponessian dirtbag saying? Is he looking in a mirror?

258
00:18:30,640 --> 00:18:34,940
Explain what Antonis? Someone got lost, we tried to help he and he says...

259
00:18:34,940 --> 00:18:37,400
..."it was here where the historical congress of Volvi took place"...

260
00:18:37,400 --> 00:18:40,760
...and I tell him "I'm not sure". And then Panos got 
involved and they started fighting.

261
00:18:40,760 --> 00:18:43,620
Yes Antonis! Because of the congress.

262
00:18:43,620 --> 00:18:47,340
- He won't believe us even if we swear on the Bible.
- What did he tell you?

263
00:18:47,340 --> 00:18:50,860
- He asked me "since when is Panos involved in politics?". And I tell him...

264
00:18:50,860 --> 00:18:52,800
..."politics never gave us anything."

265
00:18:52,800 --> 00:18:55,160
If we don't work there is no PASOK to feed us.

266
00:18:55,160 --> 00:18:58,300
Well said! And you hang up on him too.

267
00:18:58,300 --> 00:19:00,680
I didn't hang up, he did. "Because" he said...

268
00:19:00,680 --> 00:19:03,020
..."I'm not paying for the mobile line to listen to your bullshit".

269
00:19:03,020 --> 00:19:05,880
Filthy mouth! Filth!

270
00:19:05,880 --> 00:19:07,480
- Good day.
 - Good day.

271
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:09,060
- Good day too you.
 - Good day.

272
00:19:09,060 --> 00:19:10,840
Lift your right sleeve please.

273
00:19:10,840 --> 00:19:13,300
But... I'm alright.

274
00:19:20,800 --> 00:19:24,420
- The tent turned out nicely, thank you.
 - Oh, it was nothing.

275
00:19:24,420 --> 00:19:26,420
You see Miss, I was in the Engineer Corps.

276
00:19:26,420 --> 00:19:28,720
- We would build a bridge in one day.
- One day?

277
00:19:28,720 --> 00:19:32,280
- Yes. And when the army passed, 
we would tear it down again.
- Why?

278
00:19:32,280 --> 00:19:35,080
So that the enemy would not pass as well.

279
00:19:35,680 --> 00:19:39,860
- Twelve over eight.
- Your brother in law has the blood pressure of a teenager.

280
00:19:39,860 --> 00:19:41,680
So, you are leaving?

281
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:44,740
Well, yes. The family is waiting you see.

282
00:19:45,500 --> 00:19:47,100
- Good day.
- Good day.

283
00:19:49,180 --> 00:19:51,140
- Good day.
- Good day.

284
00:19:58,820 --> 00:20:02,840
You got away with it Panos,
but I shouldn't have stopped.

285
00:20:02,840 --> 00:20:06,300
When you saw the girl and yelled "stop" 
I should have stepped on the gas.

286
00:20:06,300 --> 00:20:08,940
- As if it was her fault.
- She caused your destabilization.

287
00:20:08,940 --> 00:20:10,500
Get to your senses!

288
00:20:10,500 --> 00:20:11,980
It was he who destabilized me!

289
00:20:11,980 --> 00:20:16,040
Because he wants to trap us. So that we take care of the 
seniors while he goes spearfishing.

290
00:20:16,040 --> 00:20:21,180
- Indeed, he might have thought of that.
- Yes, but what he has not thought of
 is that I might get crazy...

291
00:20:21,180 --> 00:20:23,580
...and throttle his mommy at the central square.

292
00:20:29,650 --> 00:20:36,090
- Is that radio?
 - CD.
 - Again, good day to you.


293
00:20:46,480 --> 00:20:48,680
Panos, leave Antonis to God.

294
00:20:48,680 --> 00:20:50,680
We need to get back to our families.

295
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:53,250
He will sail and he will ask the strangers...

296
00:20:53,250 --> 00:20:56,850
..."have you seen my brothers in law?" And no one will know to tell him.

297
00:20:56,850 --> 00:20:59,020
And he will come back alone, like a dog.

298
00:20:59,020 --> 00:21:01,020
I will destroy his mental health!

299
00:21:01,020 --> 00:21:05,200
- Panos, he will send Marika and Georgia to sail to take revenge.
- Our wives?!
- Yes Panos.

300
00:21:05,200 --> 00:21:08,310
And they will ask the strangers and no one will know to tell them.

301
00:21:08,310 --> 00:21:10,890
And they will go home at midnight and the children will cry...

302
00:21:10,890 --> 00:21:15,740
...and he will laugh in secret and his mental health will be just fine.
- You think he will play us like that?

303
00:21:15,740 --> 00:21:19,560
Panos, Antonis grew up in PASOK, that's like PASOK 101.

304
00:21:21,910 --> 00:21:25,070
But, Panagiotis, sometimes I think he is not that bad...

305
00:21:25,070 --> 00:21:28,050
...he works all day for the Party and at night he sells olive oil...

306
00:21:28,050 --> 00:21:30,050
...and during the weekend he reads.

307
00:21:30,050 --> 00:21:32,220
- Who works like that?
- He cakes up though!

308
00:21:32,220 --> 00:21:35,600
He does cake up but he also lends us a lot and 
we always say "you'll get it next month".

309
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:38,940
- Yeah, so what? Is he not going to get it?
- He is, but we are behind...

310
00:21:38,940 --> 00:21:41,470
...and, we also said to ask for a new loan...

311
00:21:41,470 --> 00:21:43,560
...and we will pay the grand sum.
- Better for him...

312
00:21:43,560 --> 00:21:46,540
...because if he gets it all at once, he will invest it in one place and make an impact.

313
00:21:46,540 --> 00:21:48,270
Small sums have no impact!

314
00:21:48,270 --> 00:21:54,180
One night I went to his office. I saw him, and 
you must believe me Panos, I saw him 
sitting alone on the chair.

315
00:21:54,180 --> 00:21:59,380
And I thought to myself "this man might be destined for something greater".

316
00:22:00,800 --> 00:22:01,960
It's coming again...

317
00:22:04,400 --> 00:22:07,340
- What is coming Panos?
- The thought of her...

318
00:22:07,340 --> 00:22:09,200
...I'm trying to get her out of my head, but she is coming.

319
00:22:09,200 --> 00:22:10,580
How is it coming Panagiotis?

320
00:22:10,580 --> 00:22:12,580
- I see her in front of me, looking at me.
- Looking at you?

321
00:22:12,580 --> 00:22:15,600
Yes. Now I turn my head...

322
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:18,580
...and, normally, there should be the lake...

323
00:22:18,580 --> 00:22:20,580
...well, I don't see any lake!
- You can't see the lake!?

324
00:22:20,580 --> 00:22:25,740
There's a whole lake there and you can't see it?!
- No.
- What do you see?

325
00:22:25,740 --> 00:22:27,420
I see her!

326
00:22:27,420 --> 00:22:31,020
Well, that's it! We are going nowhere! You will sleep for five hours at least...

327
00:22:31,020 --> 00:22:33,470
...with Ms. Doctor I will find a nice fish...

328
00:22:33,470 --> 00:22:35,470
...a catfish or a carp...

329
00:22:35,470 --> 00:22:38,180
...and grill it with lemon and oil. You will get up...

330
00:22:38,180 --> 00:22:41,200
...and you will eat to regain your strength and then at dusk...

331
00:22:41,200 --> 00:22:43,200
...we will go find our families.

332
00:23:16,720 --> 00:23:18,360
[SONG] <i>I am chuffed...</i>

333
00:23:18,360 --> 00:23:21,290
Am I chuffed?
- No Mr. Panos.

334
00:23:21,290 --> 00:23:23,200
So?

335
00:24:03,080 --> 00:24:07,040
Michalis.

336
00:24:07,040 --> 00:24:09,040
Yes Panos.

337
00:24:09,040 --> 00:24:12,710
Come every five minutes and check on me.

338
00:24:12,710 --> 00:24:14,710
Why must I come Panagiotis?

339
00:24:14,710 --> 00:24:17,910
To check if I'm still alive.

340
00:24:19,070 --> 00:24:24,760
[SONG] <i>Again, you'll see love as a prison.</i>

341
00:24:24,760 --> 00:24:32,540
<i>And you will wonder about those teary eyes.</i>

342
00:24:33,200 --> 00:24:38,540
<i>Again, you'll leave and run like mad.</i>

343
00:24:38,540 --> 00:24:40,850
Antonis, yes Antonis...

344
00:24:40,850 --> 00:24:42,850
...I called to say the following.

345
00:24:42,850 --> 00:24:46,400
Because, the situation is grave and I can't manage by myself.

346
00:24:46,400 --> 00:24:49,870
We argued because about the Congress, how many times must I tell you?

347
00:24:49,870 --> 00:24:52,360
And we are arguing about the Congress...

348
00:24:52,360 --> 00:24:55,650
...and he has a girl with him. And Panos starts speaking with her...

349
00:24:55,650 --> 00:24:58,050
...and the guy gets mad...

350
00:24:58,050 --> 00:25:00,490
...and he takes her and they leave.

351
00:25:00,490 --> 00:25:03,340
And that cost Panos dearly.

352
00:25:03,340 --> 00:25:06,890
What can I say? Should I say that we are losing him?

353
00:25:06,890 --> 00:25:14,140
<i>And I try, to forget you I try.</i>

354
00:25:14,140 --> 00:25:18,620
<i>There is no place where I can cry.</i>

355
00:26:01,320 --> 00:26:05,840
I must introduce you to an important scientist...

356
00:26:05,840 --> 00:26:12,220
...Professor Petseropoulos, lecturer of Psychology 
at the University of Washington.

357
00:26:12,220 --> 00:26:14,220
Nice to meet you.

358
00:26:17,160 --> 00:26:19,110
Nice to meet you.

359
00:26:22,050 --> 00:26:25,870
Mr. Michalis, on behalf of the KAPI of Makedonia and Thrace...

360
00:26:25,870 --> 00:26:29,780
...we congratulate you for fishing a hundred kilos worth of fish.

361
00:26:29,780 --> 00:26:32,270
We ran into a school.

362
00:26:34,670 --> 00:26:37,780
We also congratulate you about the quality of the meal.

363
00:26:41,510 --> 00:26:45,510
We drink towards the rapid restoration of your brother-in-law's health.

364
00:26:45,510 --> 00:26:48,450
We drink towards the good health of the bathers.

365
00:26:59,510 --> 00:27:02,090
Fish!

366
00:27:02,090 --> 00:27:05,110
Right away Panos, it's getting de-boned. You regained
your appetite...

367
00:27:05,110 --> 00:27:08,180
 ...and that is a
sign that you are getting better.

368
00:27:09,020 --> 00:27:11,420
Don't worry about your relative.

369
00:27:11,420 --> 00:27:15,510
He is just showing symptoms of a simple
impulse control disorder.
- I see...

370
00:27:15,510 --> 00:27:19,020
For example, a man falls in love with a woman...

371
00:27:19,020 --> 00:27:22,140
...will he destroy himself in her charm or will he control the impulse?

372
00:27:22,140 --> 00:27:23,780
He will control the impulse.

373
00:27:23,780 --> 00:27:25,340
Well done! Bravo!

374
00:27:25,340 --> 00:27:28,400
During the first stage, that person will lose his sight.

375
00:27:28,400 --> 00:27:29,910
He does Professor.

376
00:27:29,910 --> 00:27:32,760
Because he says "the lake should be here but I can't see it" and I tell him...

377
00:27:32,760 --> 00:27:35,470
...the lake is right there and you can't see it Panos?
- He can't.

378
00:27:35,470 --> 00:27:38,490
He only sees the face of the woman who is leading him to destruction.

379
00:27:38,490 --> 00:27:40,580
To save himself he must drown her in the lake.

380
00:27:40,580 --> 00:27:43,470
If not her, then any woman.

381
00:27:43,470 --> 00:27:44,620
Dear Lord!

382
00:27:48,760 --> 00:27:52,580
Dr. Sylvia is asking if you are going to use the multiplication-table method.

383
00:27:52,580 --> 00:27:54,050
Exactly.

384
00:27:54,050 --> 00:27:58,000
I will start with with the higher scale of nine-by-nine and I'll go down from there.

385
00:27:58,000 --> 00:28:00,400
If he does not answer three-by-three correctly...

386
00:28:00,400 --> 00:28:03,110
- What happens then Professor?
- Then unfortunately...

387
00:28:03,110 --> 00:28:05,910
- He has a family.
- Let's start from the middle.

388
00:28:05,910 --> 00:28:09,380
Ask him please. Five-by-five.

389
00:28:09,380 --> 00:28:11,070
Panos!

390
00:28:11,070 --> 00:28:13,110
Fish!

391
00:28:13,110 --> 00:28:15,110
But, Mr. Panos.

392
00:28:15,110 --> 00:28:16,540
It's getting de-boned Panos, patience.

393
00:28:16,540 --> 00:28:17,870
Five-by-five?

394
00:28:17,870 --> 00:28:19,870
Forty!

395
00:28:19,870 --> 00:28:22,620
<i>Not good at all.</i>

396
00:28:22,620 --> 00:28:24,980
- Oh God.
- Do not despair.

397
00:28:24,980 --> 00:28:26,490
Four-by-four.

398
00:28:26,490 --> 00:28:28,490
Panos! Four-by-four?

399
00:28:28,490 --> 00:28:29,820
Eighteen!

400
00:28:29,820 --> 00:28:33,200
<i>Better, better. He is getting close.</i>

401
00:28:33,200 --> 00:28:35,690
- A bit better.
- And now...

402
00:28:35,690 --> 00:28:38,140
...the critical three-by-three.

403
00:28:38,140 --> 00:28:40,140
Panos.

404
00:28:40,140 --> 00:28:42,670
Three times three?

405
00:28:42,670 --> 00:28:43,600
Nine!

406
00:28:52,090 --> 00:28:55,910
Thank you! Thank's a lot!

407
00:28:55,910 --> 00:29:01,020
Music! Music!

408
00:30:05,040 --> 00:30:10,080
[SONG] <i>Whoever told you that I learned...</i>

409
00:30:10,080 --> 00:30:14,760
<i>...to live without you is a liar.</i>

410
00:30:14,760 --> 00:30:20,050
<i>I'm living a nightmare. Dreams like wounds.</i>

411
00:30:20,050 --> 00:30:24,670
<i>I bring in my mind all moments...</i>

412
00:30:24,670 --> 00:30:29,560
<i>...where I wanted you to come and see.</i>

413
00:30:29,560 --> 00:30:34,360
<i>Please don't deny me that.</i>

414
00:30:39,650 --> 00:30:42,310
<i>Come and find me.</i>

415
00:30:42,310 --> 00:30:44,890
<i>Just to see...</i>

416
00:30:44,890 --> 00:30:49,820
<i>..how my life is like and feel sorry for me.</i>

417
00:30:49,820 --> 00:30:51,820
<i>Come and find me...</i>

418
00:30:51,820 --> 00:30:55,560
When you got under the van and lifted the bell I thought...

419
00:30:55,560 --> 00:30:59,200
..."This man is taking care of three children
 a wife, a father, a sick sister"...

420
00:30:59,200 --> 00:31:01,780
..."me, his friends, PAOK..."

421
00:31:01,780 --> 00:31:04,490
"...and how does life repai him? With breadcrumbs."

422
00:31:04,490 --> 00:31:07,290
...that's what I said.
- Leave me alone.

423
00:31:07,290 --> 00:31:10,450
A day will come when life will be different.

424
00:31:10,450 --> 00:31:12,940
We won't exist until then but that's all right.

425
00:31:12,940 --> 00:31:14,940
It's enough that they will remember us.

426
00:31:14,940 --> 00:31:17,380
They will remember that we were alive once.

427
00:31:22,670 --> 00:31:26,220
Pour him something so that he shuts up.

428
00:31:39,440 --> 00:31:43,880
[SONG] <i>Whoever told you that I learned...</i>

429
00:31:43,880 --> 00:31:48,450
<i>...to live without you is a liar.</i>

430
00:31:48,450 --> 00:31:52,000
<i>Thoughts like stabs in my heart</i>

431
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:54,580
We will start the business for the women.

432
00:31:54,580 --> 00:31:56,890
If they make their own money they won't pay any attention to us.

433
00:31:56,890 --> 00:31:58,890
And we will live a life we never imagined.

434
00:31:58,890 --> 00:32:02,180
They told me "Psomiadis is sucking you dry" and Eleni said...

435
00:32:02,180 --> 00:32:04,180
..."your children don't have a shirt to change."

436
00:32:04,180 --> 00:32:06,580
- What did Eleni say?!
- She is enabling our women Panos.

437
00:32:06,580 --> 00:32:10,540
Why didn't you say "Antonis is bringing in the dough day and night, how can you be ungrateful?"

438
00:32:10,540 --> 00:32:14,050
I did Panos. And she said "If Antonis had any brains he would not break his back for the Party..."

439
00:32:14,050 --> 00:32:15,600
..."he would be a minister like Tzoumakas."

440
00:32:15,600 --> 00:32:18,890
- Isn't she going to Italy to buy clothes?
- Is Thessaloniki too small to shop in?

441
00:32:18,890 --> 00:32:20,360
And the idiot still pays!

442
00:32:20,360 --> 00:32:23,960
If things were right this man would be sanctified.

443
00:32:25,160 --> 00:32:27,820
Panos, my mind stopped working.

444
00:32:27,820 --> 00:32:29,820
Do you happen to know how much six times six is?

445
00:32:29,820 --> 00:32:33,110
- Thirty-six.
- Seven times seven?
- Fifty-nine.

446
00:32:35,420 --> 00:32:40,540
<i>Come and find me to see how my life is like.</i>

447
00:32:40,540 --> 00:32:42,940
 <i>And feel sorry for me.</i>

448
00:32:42,940 --> 00:32:48,090
<i>Come and find me and maybe you will think about...</i>

449
00:32:48,090 --> 00:32:51,650
<i>...how I am dying alone if you don't come back.</i>

450
00:32:51,680 --> 00:33:06,540
<i>How I am dying alone if you don't come back.</i>
<i>How I am dying alone if you don't come back.</i>
<i>How I am dying alone... Come and find me.</i>

451
00:33:59,440 --> 00:34:01,360
Is there a refectory here?

452
00:34:01,360 --> 00:34:04,760
Yes, but it's not open yet.

453
00:34:04,760 --> 00:34:09,910
As you can see, it's dawn and we are alone.

454
00:36:56,000 --> 00:36:59,320
Do you want some music, maybe?

455
00:36:59,320 --> 00:37:02,620
Do you have the "Carmina Burana"?

456
00:37:02,620 --> 00:37:05,160
We have Angela, Kaitoula Garmpi...

457
00:37:05,160 --> 00:37:07,160
No!

458
00:37:07,420 --> 00:37:12,310
Alright. We came early because Mr. Panos...

459
00:37:12,310 --> 00:37:16,310
...wants to hear music the moment he wakes up.

