Mr. Psomiadis said the other day "Be prepared for work..."

704
00:55:12,260 --> 00:55:14,010
"...and in ten years the situation will be different."

705
00:55:14,010 --> 00:55:16,490
I will make them suffer.

706
00:55:16,490 --> 00:55:18,490
We don't want to harm anyone.

707
00:55:18,490 --> 00:55:20,940
Bet everything on thirty-six red.

708
00:55:20,940 --> 00:55:22,940
You don't mean, we will gamble, right?

709
00:55:22,940 --> 00:55:24,510
We got to here and won't gamble?

710
00:55:24,510 --> 00:55:27,910
We don't have money Panos. 
If Antonis does not lend us we are in dire straights.

711
00:55:27,910 --> 00:55:29,660
Next month we have to pay...

712
00:55:29,660 --> 00:55:31,040
...two rents, insurance...

713
00:55:31,040 --> 00:55:33,660
...phone and power bills. Income tax.

714
00:55:33,660 --> 00:55:35,740
We have to buy raw metal. Clothes for the kids.

715
00:55:35,740 --> 00:55:37,740
Stuff for the household.

716
00:55:37,740 --> 00:55:39,740
Take a look at this miser.

717
00:55:44,400 --> 00:55:46,460
Why are you reminding me of all this?

718
00:55:46,460 --> 00:55:48,090
Do you know what I have been through?

719
00:55:48,090 --> 00:55:50,210
- What happened to you?
 - When we were coming I said...

720
00:55:50,210 --> 00:55:52,810
...Panagiotis, if you see a dog on 
a motorcycle, take it as a sign.

721
00:55:52,810 --> 00:55:54,860
Did we or did we not see the sign?

722
00:55:54,860 --> 00:55:57,960
I saw no sign, just a motorcycle 
with four dogs running after it.

723
00:55:57,960 --> 00:55:59,760
Well, motorcycle and dog, that was the sign.

724
00:55:59,760 --> 00:56:00,940
Four dogs? Even better.

725
00:56:00,940 --> 00:56:03,690
But why thirty-six red? We have no sign for that.

726
00:56:03,690 --> 00:56:07,090
What was the weather like on St. Antons even
 when we lit the forge?

727
00:56:07,090 --> 00:56:10,390
- Snowstorm.
- Did the door open and you asked who it was?

728
00:56:10,390 --> 00:56:11,540
I did Panos because I got scared...

729
00:56:11,540 --> 00:56:13,410
...the door was loked from the inside, how did it open?

730
00:56:13,410 --> 00:56:15,290
- Did we see a woman?
- She was tall and slim and...

731
00:56:15,290 --> 00:56:17,210
...she ordered thirty-six candleholders.

732
00:56:17,210 --> 00:56:19,760
Did she sign the check as "Joan Pappos, Nevada"?

733
00:56:19,760 --> 00:56:21,760
- We cashed it.
- Did she ever come for the candleholders?

734
00:56:21,760 --> 00:56:23,360
No, and we had to sell them.

735
00:56:23,360 --> 00:56:25,860
Did they say that that night, 
many saw the Holy Mother...

736
00:56:25,860 --> 00:56:27,360
...and a lame guy got healed?

737
00:56:27,360 --> 00:56:29,160
As did a woman in Kalamaria.

738
00:56:29,160 --> 00:56:31,160
So?

739
00:56:36,610 --> 00:56:39,210
Your bets please.

740
00:56:41,260 --> 00:56:44,740
Why the hell are you betting everything on black? To jinx me?

741
00:56:45,760 --> 00:56:48,240
To have a second out, Panos.

742
00:56:49,890 --> 00:56:52,760
No more bets please.

743
00:56:57,590 --> 00:56:59,540
Seventeen, black.

744
00:57:26,800 --> 00:57:30,400
 No more bets please.

745
00:57:33,520 --> 00:57:35,990
 Seventeen, black.

746
00:57:35,990 --> 00:57:37,990
Répétition.

747
00:58:11,760 --> 00:58:13,920
No more bets please.

748
00:58:31,060 --> 00:58:33,710
Will you look at the imbecile betting on 36 red?

749
00:58:33,710 --> 00:58:35,710
Not even we could pull this off.

750
00:58:46,740 --> 00:58:48,840
36 red.

751
00:58:56,040 --> 00:58:59,360
That's motherfucking it! I'm voting for PASOK!

752
00:59:05,280 --> 00:59:07,000
Your bets please.

753
00:59:18,840 --> 00:59:21,140
 Even if I tell you Panos, you would not believe it.

754
00:59:21,140 --> 00:59:23,560
Six times répétition for 36!

755
00:59:23,560 --> 00:59:25,290
Like it was enchanted or something.

756
00:59:25,290 --> 00:59:27,690
The croupier asked me if we are related to him.

757
00:59:27,690 --> 00:59:30,690
I told him "He is our brother-in-law, Antonis". And he says...

758
00:59:30,690 --> 00:59:32,940
"We haven't seen such a good player in ages."

759
00:59:32,940 --> 00:59:33,960
You know why he said that?

760
00:59:33,960 --> 00:59:35,510
Because he tipped the shit out of him.

761
00:59:35,510 --> 00:59:38,360
No, Panos. I was in charge of tipping.

762
00:59:38,360 --> 00:59:40,460
I pretended throwing them a chip...

763
00:59:40,460 --> 00:59:42,040
...they said "Thank you"...

764
00:59:42,040 --> 00:59:44,040
...and I put the chip back in my pocket.

765
00:59:51,140 --> 00:59:53,510
 We are broke, we can't tip.

766
01:00:05,740 --> 01:00:07,760
Squeeze her tight you redneck.

767
01:00:07,760 --> 01:00:10,360
But watch out for any dangerous swelling.

768
01:00:10,360 --> 01:00:13,040
Panos, let them be.

769
01:00:13,040 --> 01:00:14,790
Antonis saved us.

770
01:00:14,790 --> 01:00:19,560
And Clytemnestra, could be the woman every man dreams of meeting once in his life.

771
01:00:19,560 --> 01:00:22,560
You are payed off, right? He payed you to sweet-talk me.

772
01:00:22,560 --> 01:00:27,610
Tell me, the rat saw the cheese, but did he see the trap?

773
01:00:27,610 --> 01:00:29,290
What do you mean, Panos?

774
01:00:29,290 --> 01:00:32,990
They let him win today, so that tomorrow he loses twice as much.

775
01:00:32,990 --> 01:00:34,040
And the chick...

776
01:00:34,040 --> 01:00:36,360
...once they suck him dry, she is gone.

777
01:00:39,540 --> 01:00:40,990
Won't you eat your eggs?

778
01:00:43,460 --> 01:00:46,460
That half-wit fuck boy.

779
01:00:46,460 --> 01:00:48,810
We gathered you all here, stupid southerners...

780
01:00:48,810 --> 01:00:51,040
...and you are stealing our bread.

781
01:01:06,280 --> 01:01:08,400
Panos, I wonder...

782
01:01:08,400 --> 01:01:11,810
...if this Ms. Joan Pappos comes back one day...

783
01:01:11,810 --> 01:01:13,810
...and asks for the candleholders.

784
01:01:24,800 --> 01:01:26,760
What did he tell you when you woke him up?

785
01:01:26,760 --> 01:01:30,140
He says he will be down in half an hour. I leave, they ask for Mr. Arbouzoglou.

786
01:01:30,140 --> 01:01:32,610
I pick up the phone again, he asks "did you have breakfast yet?"

787
01:01:32,610 --> 01:01:34,410
I say, "no".

788
01:01:34,410 --> 01:01:36,460
He says, "Get some and charge it to room 331".

789
01:01:36,460 --> 01:01:38,840
Empty gestures like that are the shepherd's favorite.

790
01:01:38,840 --> 01:01:40,610
Nevertheless, he thought about us, Panos.

791
01:01:40,610 --> 01:01:44,760
Because, people who bask in their happiness usually don't think of others.

792
01:01:44,760 --> 01:01:48,060
Tell me, do you remember the code-word?

793
01:02:01,400 --> 01:02:03,960
Now, you think we mean you harm?

794
01:02:03,960 --> 01:02:06,090
That we don't want you to enjoy yourself a bit?

795
01:02:06,090 --> 01:02:08,610
That we are not your brothers-in-law?

796
01:02:08,610 --> 01:02:10,840
Isn't it you who takes care of the elders and my sisters?

797
01:02:10,840 --> 01:02:12,760
Isn't it you who pays for the study help for the kids?

798
01:02:12,760 --> 01:02:15,310
- Didn't you go to the taxman...
 - Didn't you go to the taxman to save us?

799
01:02:15,310 --> 01:02:16,440
You told him...

800
01:02:16,440 --> 01:02:18,040
"If those two poor souls..."

801
01:02:18,040 --> 01:02:22,010
"...who work since they were twelve, neglected to VAT once or twice, are guilty..."

802
01:02:22,010 --> 01:02:24,190
"...then half of Greece should be behind bars."

803
01:02:24,190 --> 01:02:26,390
And he tells you "I am just doing my job".

804
01:02:26,390 --> 01:02:29,760
And you tell him "PASOK came to teach you that you job is..."

805
01:02:29,760 --> 01:02:31,940
"...to stand next to the people and solve their problems."

806
01:02:31,940 --> 01:02:34,740
- And I go to the taxman...
- And I go to the taxman...

807
01:02:34,740 --> 01:02:37,540
...and he tells me "what a magnificent person that brother-in-law of yours."

808
01:02:37,540 --> 01:02:40,090
"It is people like that who should govern us!" And I think to myself...

809
01:02:40,090 --> 01:02:42,910
Antonis, I wish your mother was here to hear this...

810
01:02:42,910 --> 01:02:45,760
...and rejoice, that poor woman.

811
01:03:06,340 --> 01:03:08,210
Yes, but you vote for New Democracy.

812
01:03:08,210 --> 01:03:09,740
That is indeed true.

813
01:03:09,740 --> 01:03:11,140
Other party memebers say...

814
01:03:11,140 --> 01:03:13,360
..."Not even your brothers-in-law vote for PASOK..."

815
01:03:13,360 --> 01:03:14,660
"...and you dream of becoming MP?"

816
01:03:14,660 --> 01:03:15,860
And you didn't flip them off?

817
01:03:15,860 --> 01:03:18,610
Who told you this? I'll deck his face and teach him not to be ignorant.

818
01:03:18,610 --> 01:03:20,190
They are being ignorant.

819
01:03:20,190 --> 01:03:21,790
I'll tell him "Come here you ashole.."

820
01:03:21,790 --> 01:03:23,940
"...Did you even ask why I have to vote for New Democracy?"

821
01:03:23,940 --> 01:03:26,640
If Psomiadis told you "Cut the crap and vote for my grandson..."

822
01:03:26,640 --> 01:03:29,190
"...because I put bread on your table and not PASOK", what would you do?

823
01:03:29,190 --> 01:03:32,310
That, if he didn't work with you, two families would out in the street?

824
01:03:32,310 --> 01:03:34,210
Relax, your blood pressure will spike again.

825
01:03:34,210 --> 01:03:37,410
Let is spike! Let it reach 24, let me die right here in front of him!

826
01:03:37,410 --> 01:03:39,510
Look how they divide us.

827
01:03:39,510 --> 01:03:41,510
And Psomiades comes, elections eve...

828
01:03:41,510 --> 01:03:44,160
...and brings some Touloubes and some sealed election sheets.

829
01:03:44,160 --> 01:03:46,160
And I count the sheets and ask him "Mr. Vasilis..."

830
01:03:46,160 --> 01:03:48,690
"...me, plus my wife, my father and my sister is four..."

831
01:03:48,690 --> 01:03:52,060
"...plus Michails, his wife and his mother, that's seven..."

832
01:03:52,060 --> 01:03:53,010
"...Why eight sheets?"

833
01:03:53,010 --> 01:03:55,860
And he says "What about the mother of your in-law, Antonis."

834
01:04:05,790 --> 01:04:09,360
So, my mother voted for New Democracy?

835
01:04:09,360 --> 01:04:10,890
What were my options, Antonis?

836
01:04:10,890 --> 01:04:13,460
I took her to the station, gave her the election sheet...

837
01:04:13,460 --> 01:04:15,990
...and told her "Ms. Vasiliki, Antonis said to vote it."

838
01:04:15,990 --> 01:04:18,140
She crossed herself, kissed it..

839
01:04:18,140 --> 01:04:20,090
...corssed it as well thrice...

840
01:04:20,090 --> 01:04:22,090
...and threw it in the ballot box!

841
01:04:26,640 --> 01:04:29,790
Antonis, woohoo!

842
01:04:29,790 --> 01:04:32,310
Clytemnestra, woohoo!

843
01:04:32,310 --> 01:04:35,860
Antonis, look it's Clytemnestra. Woohoo!

844
01:04:37,440 --> 01:04:39,560
Father...

845
01:04:45,400 --> 01:04:50,080
Clytemnestra, help! Clytemnestra, help!

846
01:05:07,000 --> 01:05:09,060
 - Woe us.
 - We came Mr. Michalis

847
01:05:09,060 --> 01:05:12,310
...because Ms. Clytemnestra called us and told us where you are.

848
01:05:12,310 --> 01:05:14,310
They throwing two families to the streets.

849
01:05:14,310 --> 01:05:18,140
We hired a cab so that we can entertain you.

850
01:05:25,000 --> 01:05:26,960
Help me.

851
01:05:28,940 --> 01:05:31,240
The jacket! Take off his jacket!

852
01:05:31,240 --> 01:05:33,240
Take it off.

853
01:05:37,440 --> 01:05:42,110
Michalis!

854
01:05:42,110 --> 01:05:45,710
Hang the jacket somewhere.

855
01:05:47,080 --> 01:05:51,200
Let him get some air. Why did you do this to us Antonis?

856
01:05:51,640 --> 01:05:55,210
Such good people...

857
01:05:55,210 --> 01:05:57,210
...yet such a drama.

858
01:05:57,210 --> 01:06:01,260
<i>It has been a month.</i>

859
01:06:01,260 --> 01:06:05,210
<i>The machines are gathering rust...</i>

860
01:06:05,210 --> 01:06:10,910
<i>...and the children are cold and hungry.</i>

861
01:06:14,040 --> 01:06:22,160
<i>Flyers are handed out in the streets of Athens.</i>

862
01:06:22,160 --> 01:06:28,310
<i>Workers are asking for solidarity.</i>

863
01:06:30,740 --> 01:06:38,510
<i>Flyers are handed out in the streets of Athens.</i>

864
01:06:38,510 --> 01:06:45,660
<i>Workers are asking for solidarity.</i>

865
01:06:51,990 --> 01:06:55,240
That which comes as an evolution in labor relations...

866
01:06:55,240 --> 01:06:57,060
...could be something unknown...

867
01:06:57,060 --> 01:06:58,440
...and beyond our comprehension.

868
01:06:58,440 --> 01:07:00,860
Michalis!

869
01:07:00,860 --> 01:07:05,760
The children of the future will grow up in a new reality...

870
01:07:05,760 --> 01:07:07,940
...a reality, which we will propably never know.

871
01:07:07,940 --> 01:07:10,190
Michalis!

872
01:07:10,190 --> 01:07:12,190
I'm busy Panos.

873
01:07:13,660 --> 01:07:18,210
In this critical moment, PASOK is the only party that can stand beside the people...

874
01:07:18,210 --> 01:07:21,260
...and lead them to the threshold of this new world...

875
01:07:21,260 --> 01:07:24,460
...without having to sink them into despair and marginalize them.

876
01:07:24,460 --> 01:07:25,690
See?

877
01:07:25,690 --> 01:07:28,110
We have never heard such nice words like that.

878
01:07:28,110 --> 01:07:30,110
Who will tell them to us?

879
01:07:30,110 --> 01:07:32,810
The Right is not discoursing in the level of ideas...

880
01:07:32,810 --> 01:07:36,140
...but, stuck to the old mentality, they prefer to bribe the souls of the people.

881
01:07:36,140 --> 01:07:36,910
Exactly!

882
01:07:36,910 --> 01:07:39,440
In the meanwhile, us, you tell us to help with the elections...

883
01:07:39,440 --> 01:07:41,840
...so, we ask "where do you want your child to be positioned in?"

884
01:07:41,840 --> 01:07:43,940
Or, "Do you need a loan?", to keep the people happy.

885
01:07:43,940 --> 01:07:46,460
Well done Mr. Panos!

886
01:07:46,460 --> 01:07:48,940
Remember in Stavroupoli? You call us...

887
01:07:48,940 --> 01:07:51,740
..."Come lift Venizelos up to the stage".

888
01:07:51,740 --> 01:07:54,760
And when you got off the Mercedes me and Michalis picked him up...

889
01:07:54,760 --> 01:07:57,410
...and it is since that day I have this backpain.

890
01:07:57,410 --> 01:07:59,660
You sacrificed a lot.

891
01:07:59,660 --> 01:08:01,660
But, how can I tell my father...

892
01:08:01,660 --> 01:08:03,860
...that mother voted for New Democracy?

893
01:08:03,860 --> 01:08:07,090
But Antonis, your father has been dead for 25 years.

894
01:08:07,660 --> 01:08:10,210
He was an anti-authoritarian in Papaditsa.

895
01:08:10,210 --> 01:08:13,740
He was drinking his coffee alone in the village square and then he came home.

896
01:08:13,740 --> 01:08:15,840
His mother would say...

897
01:08:15,840 --> 01:08:18,890
..."Giannis, don't despair that no one is saying hello to you."

898
01:08:18,890 --> 01:08:20,890
"You forgive them."

899
01:08:22,340 --> 01:08:29,440
When in 1982, on St. Johns day, his namesday, he came into my dream, I told him...

900
01:08:29,440 --> 01:08:31,160
"Father..."

901
01:08:31,160 --> 01:08:33,440
"...the blessed day has come!"

902
01:08:33,440 --> 01:08:35,990
"The People now have the power in their hands!"

903
01:08:35,990 --> 01:08:39,710
Mr. Antonis, we vote for New Democracy...

904
01:08:39,710 --> 01:08:42,460
...but, now that we have heard the story of your dad...

905
01:08:42,460 --> 01:08:44,890
...we will vote for PASOK.

906
01:08:44,890 --> 01:08:46,890
Right Archontoula?

907
01:08:50,400 --> 01:08:53,320
When I tell you he was not feeling well, you better believe me.

908
01:08:53,320 --> 01:08:55,910
Yes, similar to the one Panos had but a bit less serious.

909
01:08:55,910 --> 01:08:57,910
Now he is giving a speech.

910
01:08:57,910 --> 01:09:02,540
Of course he is giving a speech, you never know when elections might pop up!

911
01:09:02,540 --> 01:09:04,140
We start in half an hour.

912
01:09:04,140 --> 01:09:06,840
If we are having the lamb, start with it now.

913
01:09:06,840 --> 01:09:10,140
And we can reheat it if we arrive too late.

914
01:09:10,140 --> 01:09:12,140
All right, Eleni.

915
01:09:12,760 --> 01:09:15,910
Antonis, with Panos we will arrange for some quality fish.

916
01:09:15,910 --> 01:09:17,060
I don't want fish.

917
01:09:17,060 --> 01:09:18,410
What do you want?

918
01:09:18,410 --> 01:09:19,140
Kokoretsi.

919
01:09:19,140 --> 01:09:20,240
Kokoretsi?

920
01:09:20,240 --> 01:09:21,490
Leave it up to me.

921
01:09:21,490 --> 01:09:24,610
Panos, he does not want normal Kokoretsi, he wants it Papadits-style.

922
01:09:24,610 --> 01:09:27,340
Papaditsa-style, of course. Leave it up to me I said.

923
01:09:37,060 --> 01:09:41,410
<i>I will become the step that will help you rise.</i>

924
01:09:41,410 --> 01:09:45,790
<i>I will become your cry of passion.</i>

925
01:09:45,790 --> 01:09:50,910
<i>You'll love me you'll see, you'll love me.</i>

926
01:09:50,910 --> 01:09:56,060
<i>I will laugh for me. I will pay for me.</i>

927
01:09:56,060 --> 01:10:00,940
<i>Because, until this day...</i>

928
01:10:00,940 --> 01:10:02,940
Two thousand one hundred seventy.

929
01:10:02,940 --> 01:10:04,360
Two thousand one hundred eighty.

930
01:10:04,360 --> 01:10:06,360
Two thousand one hundred ninety.

931
01:10:06,360 --> 01:10:08,010
Two thousand two hundred.

932
01:10:08,010 --> 01:10:09,940
Two thousand two hundred ten.

933
01:10:09,940 --> 01:10:11,610
Two thousand two hundred twenty.

934
01:10:11,610 --> 01:10:13,190
Two thousand two hundred thirty.

935
01:10:13,190 --> 01:10:14,690
Two thousand two hundred forty.

936
01:10:14,690 --> 01:10:17,460
Two thousand two hundred fifty.

937
01:10:17,460 --> 01:10:21,060
<i>...everything I did, I did for you.</i>

938
01:10:22,310 --> 01:10:23,360
That's enough.

939
01:10:23,360 --> 01:10:24,310
Mister, still dirty.

940
01:10:24,310 --> 01:10:27,890
Get done with it! I want them dirty goddammit!

941
01:10:27,890 --> 01:10:29,440
Damn Albanians...

942
01:10:29,440 --> 01:10:33,040
...we let you wander around and you steal the peoples bread!

943
01:10:36,240 --> 01:10:39,160
You will eat the Papaditsa-style Kokoretsi to regain yourself.

944
01:10:39,160 --> 01:10:41,440
And once you feel better, we start to meet our families.

945
01:10:41,440 --> 01:10:45,440
What are you talking about? Did you ask him if he is in the state to travel?

946
01:10:45,440 --> 01:10:47,060
I don't have any cash left.

947
01:10:47,060 --> 01:10:47,810
It got wet.

948
